\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jvb1665703130778.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jvb1665703130778.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jvb1665703130778.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jvb1665703130778\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger store\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__section_w317ab1b7b1_w318ab1b7_w319ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__table_d14681e1_d14682e1_d14683e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger store</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Activated by the structure editor function\n                        ^STORE. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Implicitly validates all unvalidated fields,\n                        keys and occurrences and then executes <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">done</span>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__section_w320ab1b7b3_w321ab1b7_w322ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d187027e132\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__p_d118049e1_d118050e1_d118051e1\">By default, the store trigger contains the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement with ProcScript to check for any store errors. If the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> action was successful, it commits the stored data; otherwise, the changes are rolled back.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__p_d118052e1_d118053e1_d118054e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement activates the following triggers:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__li_d44858e1_d44859e1_d44860e1\">write or writeUp trigger of each occurrence that has been modified or newly entered. Unmodified occurrences are not stored.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__li_d44861e1_d44862e1_d44863e1\">Delete or deleteUp trigger of each occurrence that has been removed.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jvb1665703130778__p_d118055e1_d118056e1_d118057e1\">If you want to prevent the user from storing occurrences with certain values, you should put the checks in the field loseFocus trigger, and the leaveModified and leaveModifiedKey triggers. This approach allows the user to be informed about the error at the point of data entry, rather than later when the data is stored. The write trigger is an alternative place for these checks, but is not recommended.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nua1719397360028.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>delete</a><p>Deletes the current occurrence from the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kgi1665702560769.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>store</a><p>Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nht1665702561308.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>write</a><p>Write the current occurrence to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mfn1665703129379.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger delete</a><p>Removes occurrences marked for deletion, when writing updates to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkk1665702703541.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger deleteUp</a><p>System trigger that handles deletion of Up entity occurrences. (An Up entity is an inner entity that represents the One side in a one-to-many relationship.)</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wbv1665702600112.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger loseFocus (Field)</a><p>Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/emi1665702599671.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger leaveModifiedKey</a><p>Location for ProcScript that determines what happens after a key (especially a compound key) of an occurrence is modified. Applicable only in form components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xmm1665702603717.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger leaveModified</a><p>Trigger that handles processing after the user moves to another occurrence in a form, after having modified the original occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjr1665703129938.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger write</a><p>System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence is written to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rog1665702561386.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger writeUp</a><p>System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence of an Up entity must be written to the database.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529064\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529064\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger store Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger store Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data. Declaration: trigger store Applies to: Form Activation: Activated by the structure editor function ^STORE. Default behavior: Implicitly validates all unvalidated fields, keys and occurrences and then executes done . Behavior upon completion: None Description By default, the store trigger contains the store statement with ProcScript to check for any store errors. If the store action was successful, it commits the stored data; otherwise, the changes are rolled back. The store statement activates the following triggers: write or writeUp trigger of each occurrence that has been modified or newly entered. Unmodified occurrences are not stored. Delete or deleteUp trigger of each occurrence that has been removed. If you want to prevent the user from storing occurrences with certain values, you should put the checks in the field loseFocus trigger, and the leaveModified and leaveModifiedKey triggers. This approach allows the user to be informed about the error at the point of data entry, rather than later when the data is stored. The write trigger is an alternative place for these checks, but is not recommended. Related Links delete Deletes the current occurrence from the database. store Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers. write Write the current occurrence to the database. trigger delete Removes occurrences marked for deletion, when writing updates to the database. trigger deleteUp System trigger that handles deletion of Up entity occurrences. (An Up entity is an inner entity that represents the One side in a one-to-many relationship.) trigger loseFocus (Field) Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component. trigger leaveModifiedKey Location for ProcScript that determines what happens after a key (especially a compound key) of an occurrence is modified. Applicable only in form components. trigger leaveModified Trigger that handles processing after the user moves to another occurrence in a form, after having modified the original occurrence. trigger write System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence is written to the database. trigger writeUp System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence of an Up entity must be written to the database. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}